abstract: Protesters angered by a local result in Tunisia’s first free election burned a central government building on Friday in the impoverished town of Sidi Bouzid, widely regarded as the birthplace of the Arab Spring; violence appears to have been set off by a local election issue, rather than displeasure at the results of the national vote.
